    "content": "Step 8 mini-retro action items look good. Standardizing \"CONSENSUS: APPROVED\" as the first line will help with tallying.\n\n**On Step 9 — Clarify as Waiting For:**\n\nProduct context: This is the \"clarify as delegated\" path from US-GTD-2, which says users can mark an inbox item as \"actionable and delegated -> move to Waiting For with a note about who/what.\" This connects the inbox clarify workflow to the Waiting For list we just built in Step 8.\n\nThe pattern should follow what we did for \"Clarify as Next Action\" (Step 5) and \"Clarify as Project\" (Step 7) — an option on the clarify form that routes the inbox item to Waiting For, collecting the waiting_on field in the process. The inbox item is consumed (deleted from inbox) and a new WaitingForItem is created.\n\nI support Luca continuing as Driver — he built the Waiting For infrastructure and the clarify patterns in prior steps, so he has the most context. No reason to rotate for a feature that directly extends his work.\n\nOne product note: This step also completes the \"convert a Waiting For item to a Next Action\" acceptance criterion we deferred from US-GTD-5. Make sure that gets included in Step 9's scope or is tracked separately so it doesn't fall through the cracks."
  }
}
